Preheat your oven to 200°C. Pop the @sweet potato fries{250%g} on a #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @olive oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat then spread out and bake on the top shelf of the oven for ~{18%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Lay a @British chicken breasts{2} on the #chopping board{}, place your hand flat on top and slice into it from the side.

Be careful not to slice all the way through. Open it up like a book. Repeat for the other breast(s).

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Zest the @lime{1/2}(zested), then halve the lime. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}(grated) and keep to one side. Trim and peel the @beetroot{1}, then coarsely grate.

> TIP: Wear gloves when handling the beetroot to avoid staining your hands!

Pop the grated beetroot into a #bowl{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir in the @olive oil{1%tbsp} and the juice of the lime. Keep to one side.

Heat a splash of oil in a large #frying pan{} over high heat. Season the butterflied chicken breasts with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When the oil is hot, lay the chicken in the pan and brown for ~{2%minutes} on both sides.

Once browned, lower the heat to medium and cook for another ~{4-5%minutes} on each side.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, mix the cheddar cheese with the @BBQ sauce{32%g} and lime zest in a small bowl.

When the chicken is cooked, spread the cheesy BBQ sauce on top of the chicken and cover the pan with a #lid{} or #plate{}.

Cook until the cheese has melted, a further ~{1%minute} or so. Halve the @burger buns{2} and get ready to plate up.

Share the fries between your plates. Pop a cheesy BBQ chicken breast inside each bun.

Add the beetroot slaw to the burger bun or serve it on the side. It's up to you! Enjoy!